cluster_relations.rel_desc: The duration of a butterfly's adult lifespan varies depending on the butterfly species.
Communication platforms and media enable or support the rapid transmission of information.
remarks: Semantics partially inferred from typical communication dynamics.

cluster_relations.rel_desc: The authenticity of urban legends determines or reflects the truth behind the stories.
In urban legend tales, the line between fact and fiction is often blurred.
AI systems are trained on specific training data, which determines their quality.

qualifiers.OtherQualifier: QualityDependency: performance linked to training data quality

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the value or characteristics of the subject are determined or constrained by the type or identity of the object.
args.justification: The description states that butterfly adult lifespan duration varies depending on the butterfly species, which is a dependency of a trait on species identity.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject makes it possible for, or facilitates, the occurrence or efficiency of the object process or outcome.
args.justification: Communication platforms and media are described as enabling or supporting the rapid transmission of information, which is a standard enabling/facilitation relation.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject affects, shapes, or constrains the nature, degree, or assessment of the object.
args.justification: The authenticity of urban legends is described as determining or reflecting the truth behind the stories; this is best captured as an influence relation between authenticity and perceived truth.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the conceptual boundary represented by the subject becomes indistinct or unclear within the narrative or situational context represented by the object.
args.justification: The line between fact and fiction is said to be often blurred in the context of urban legend tales; this is a contextual state-change of the boundary within the proliferation of urban legends.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject AI system has been fitted or learned from the dataset represented by the object during a training process.
args.justification: The relation explicitly states that AI systems are trained on specific training data; this is a standard machine learning training predicate.
The relation captures how a biological trait (adult lifespan) depends on species identity, fitting a class of dependencies between traits and categorical factors.
The subject provides a capability (communication platform) that enables a particular process (rapid transmission of information), which is an enabling-type relation.
The authenticity of urban legends affects judgments about the truth behind stories, representing a conceptual influence between abstract narrative properties.
The relation concerns the state of the boundary between fact and fiction within a narrative context, fitting a class of relations about narrative truth boundaries.
The relation specifies which data an AI system is trained on, fitting a class of ML training and data–model relations.

All three relations describe a dependency or influence where the subject affects or enables the object: (1) trait depends on species, (2) platforms enable information flow, (3) authenticity influences perceived truth.

The relation describes a qualitative modification of the subject (the line between fact and fiction becoming blurred) under a particular narrative context, fitting a modification/state-change dimension.
Training data is used by the AI system during the training process; this is best modeled as a usage/consumption relation between system and data.
